  <summary date="2019-03-25T16:12:58Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Lessen Impediments From Taxes for Charities Act or the LIFT for Charities Act 

This bill modifies the requirements for determining the unrelated business taxable income of tax-exempt organizations. The bill repeals a provision that requires unrelated business taxable income to be increased by the amount of expenses paid or incurred by a tax-exempt organization for certain fringe benefits for which a tax deduction is not allowed, including benefits relating to transportation, parking, or an on-premises athletic facility.</summary>
